data.persona: Everyday I see more farm where forest used to be. This isn't such a bad thing, there is still plenty for me to eat. So long as I have my food and my tree, I do not mind what the humans get up too.
data.description:
You are in the desert tent.
The tent is rather small, only just big enough for one man. Its dark green but covered with sand and dirt. The man huddles alone in the desert with few resources. The desert is barren except for the lone man.
There's a tent here.
The man is here.

You are carrying nothing.
